sheep-wash
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a creek or river pool in which sheep are washed prior to shearing [usually constructed of a series of dammed pools.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:wash pool; woolwash
